  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden, then set aside and reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684234867537-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684234867537-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684234867537-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684234867537-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684234867537-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pine nuts are toasting, trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and chop into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into large chunks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684234871328-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684234871328-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684234871328-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684234871328-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684234871328-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat the reserved pan with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped aubergine</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the veg is starting to brown</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684234875935-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684234875935-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684234875935-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684234875935-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684234875935-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg is starting to brown, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>sultanas </strong>and <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and cook for 1 min or until the vinegar has evaporated</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684234879069-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684234879069-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684234879069-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684234879069-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684234879069-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vinegar has evaporated, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the veg is tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684234882740-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684234882740-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684234882740-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684234882740-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684234882740-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the veg is cooking, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add your <strong>couscous</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a heatproof bowl with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, cover and set aside until all of the liquid has been absorbed</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684234886372-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684234886372-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684234886372-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684234886372-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684234886372-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg is tender, add your <strong>capers </strong>to the pan and cook, uncovered, for a final 2 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened – this is your <strong>Sicilian-style aubergine stew</strong></p><p>While the sauce is thickening, fluff the <strong>cooked couscous</strong> with a fork, then stir most of the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> (save some for garnish!) and the <strong>toasted pine nuts </strong>through the couscous with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>pine nut couscous</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684234890413-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684234890413-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684234890413-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684234890413-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684234890413-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Sicilian-style aubergine stew</strong> over the <strong>pine nut couscous</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
